        "SAPA's operational model is built on <cite id=\"4\">direct service delivery</cite>, allowing them to bypass intermediaries and reduce costs. This approach results in a <cite id=\"8\">$4.87 cost per beneficiary</cite>, which is considered exceptional for global health interventions. Their financial health is further evidenced by <cite id=\"14\">4.3 months of working capital</cite>, providing a strong buffer for emergency operations. The organization also shows <cite id=\"15\">strong fundraising efficiency</cite>, spending only <cite id=\"16\">$0.11 to raise every $1</cite>."
      ],
      "summary": "The Sudanese American Physicians Association (SAPA) is a medical humanitarian organization that <cite id=\"1\">strengthens healthcare infrastructure in Sudan and Chad</cite>. founded in 2019, the organization has quickly scaled to address the collapse of medical services in conflict zones. SAPA operates with <cite id=\"2\">high financial efficiency</cite>, maintaining a <cite id=\"3\">97/100 overall score from Charity Navigator</cite>. Their work focuses on <cite id=\"4\">building core healthcare functions</cite> that can survive crises. This includes <cite id=\"5\">direct healthcare delivery, hunger relief, and WASH programs</cite> across regions like Khartoum and Blue Nile. The charity reported <cite id=\"6\">$3,502,228 in total revenue</cite> for the 2023 tax year. They demonstrate <cite id=\"7\">exceptional cost-effectiveness</cite> with an estimated cost of <cite id=\"8\">$4.87 per beneficiary</cite>. For Muslim donors, SAPA offers <cite id=\"9\">verified zakat-eligible giving options</cite> to support those in extreme need. Their rapid growth from a <cite id=\"10\">$442,259 revenue base in 2022</cite> to over $7 million in 2024 reflects a significant expansion in emergency response capacity.",
